ox.<br>
Here's a good little midge in fast water under a white indicator.  Can't for the life of me think of the name.  <br>
Hook- standard scud hook, size 18.  Thread color-matching color of flying bugs, 8/0.  Ribbing- FINE wire of choice, copper or black.  Dubbing, black or grey.  1 strand of krystal flash, pearl.  1 Glass bead for the head, clear.  This is a pretty simple pattern that has been around for a good while.  Wrap the hook with thread to the bend after putting the bead on.  Rib with fine wire.  Create a small ball of dubbing just behind the bead, about 1.5 times the size of the bead in diameter.  Add the Krystal Flash strand by tying it in just behind the bead making it appear as 2 wings.  This is done by tying it in at the center of the strand.  Whip finish and you are done.  Great little fly on the North Fork in fast water.  <br>
~Andrew <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bflyfishingarkansasandmissouri.showUserPublicProfile?gid=holland@flyfishingarkansasandmissouri>Holland</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 44<br> <font color=#000000>(9/15/03 7:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fflyfishingarkansasandmissourifrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: favorite fly</span><hr size=1> During times of no generation when things get dull and nobody's catching anything, I have gone to a 16 or 18 Brassie and come up with fish.  Usually they are pretty good ones too.  Sometimes I think I'm the only guy out there fishing Brassies anymore. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F9FBFD><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bflyfishingarkansasandmissouri.showUserPublicProfile?gid=randy@flyfishingarkansasandmissouri>randy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#000000>(9/23/03 8:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fflyfishingarkansasandmissourifrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> favorite fly</span><hr size=1> I fish a San Juan with a tungsten bead in the middle.  For fast riffles...I like to fish up from the handicapped access across from Bob Dobbin's Cabin in some shalllow, fast water.  The heavy bead puts it down at the top of my drift and rolls it along the bottom.   I like the burgandy (wine) color as well as the worm brown. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub98.ezboard.com/fflyfishingarkans